                            <comment id="15492685" author="srowen" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2016 07:54:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;hostname --fqdn&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t work on OS X, so may be specific to some versions of Linux et al. However looks like &lt;tt&gt;hostname -f&lt;/tt&gt; is a synonym on Linux, and works on OS X (though doesn&apos;t necessarily give more info). Go for it with &lt;tt&gt;-f&lt;/tt&gt; I think.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
